Write a method called isPalindrome() which takes in a string and returns true if the string is a palindrome and false if it not.
A palindrome is a word that reads the same backward as forward. Here are some examples:
isPalindrome(“racecar”) -> true
isPalindrome(“yes”) -> false
isPalindrome(“a”) -> true
isPalindrome(“”) -> true



class Main {
  public static void main(String[] args) {
    System.out.println(isPalindrome("yes"));
		System.out.println(isPalindrome("racecar"));
		System.out.println(isPalindrome("b"));
		System.out.println(isPalindrome(""));
  }

	public static boolean isPalindrome(String str) {
		for(int i = 0; i < str.length()/2; i++) {
			if(str.charAt(i) != str.charAt(str.length()-1-i)) {
				return false;
			}
		}
		return true;
	}
}
